# Asset Migration (Monolith → `assets/`)

Execute in this order. Test in browser after each step.

## 1. Create folders

```
assets/css/main.css
assets/js/main.js
assets/images/     # .gitkeep or real photos
```

## 2. Extract CSS

- Cut the `<style>` block contents from `index.html` (design tokens through responsive rules)
- Paste into `assets/css/main.css` (no `<style>` tags)
- In `index.html` `<head>`:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/main.css"/>
```

## 3. Extract JavaScript

- Cut the bottom `<script>` block into `assets/js/main.js`
- In `index.html` before `</body>`:

```html
<script src="assets/js/main.js" defer></script>
```

## 4. Images

Replace emoji placeholders:

| Location | File |
|----------|------|
| `.hero-photo` | `assets/images/technician-hero.jpg` |
| `.about-photo` | `assets/images/junior-photo.jpg` |

```html
<img src="assets/images/technician-hero.jpg" alt="Junior Solice, pest control technician" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;">
```

## 5. Contact constants (optional)

`assets/js/config.js`:

```javascript
export const PHONE_DISPLAY = '(201) XXX-XXXX';
export const PHONE_TEL = '+1XXXXXXXXXX';
export const EMAIL = 'hello@itsjustjune.com';
```

If staying script-free, search-replace phone/email in HTML after split.

## 6. Verify

- Serve via `python3 -m http.server` (not `file://`) so asset paths resolve
- Check modal, marquee pause, scroll reveal, mobile breakpoints
- Confirm Google Fonts `<link>` remains in `<head>`

## Do not

- Introduce a build tool unless the user requests it
- Change section IDs or modal behavior during extraction-only work
